<paragraph lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="3" pageNumber="16">
Six females, Russia: Tyumen Province, vicinity of Tyumen, 
<geoCoordinate direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="15" value="57.067497">57째04'03&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="15" value="65.07">65째04'12&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
, on ants 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Lasius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lasius niger" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niger">
<pageBreakToken pageId="4" pageNumber="17" start="start">Lasius</pageBreakToken>
niger
</taxonomicName>
L., 17 August 2014, coll. V.M. Salavatulin; 5 females, Russia: Tyumen Province, vicinity of Tyumen, 
<geoCoordinate direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="15" value="57.16528">57째09'55&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="15" value="65.458885">65째27'32&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
, on ants 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Lasius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lasius niger" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niger">Lasius niger</taxonomicName>
, 31 August 2014, coll. A.A. Khaustov.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="17">
This species was described from Japan where it was found in the nests of ants 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Lasius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lasius niger" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niger">Lasius niger</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Lasius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lasius hayashi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hayashi">Lasius hayashi</taxonomicName>
Yamauchi and Hayashida (
<bibRefCitation author="Kurosa, K" journalOrPublisher="Annotationes Zoologicae Japonenses" pageId="13" pageNumber="26" pagination="63 - 71" title="Three new species of Unguidispus (Acari, Heterostigmata, Microdispidae) from Japan." volume="521" year="1979">Kurosa 1979</bibRefCitation>
). I recorded phoresy of this species on 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Lasius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lasius niger" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niger">Lasius niger</taxonomicName>
in Western Siberia. This is a new record for the fauna of Russia.
</paragraph>
